{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place a nut milk bag or fine-mesh sieve over a bowl. Place bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh yoghurt into nut milk bag. Place bowl with yoghurt into refrigerator for 1 hour to drain. Discard any strained liquid.","Place a ceramic or glass bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh bread and 40 g of the water into it. Set aside to soak (approx. 10 minutes).","Place parsley, spring onions\/shallots and lemon zest into mixing bowl and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 8<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula. Transfer half of the parsley mixture into a bowl and set aside.","Add fish, egg, chilli powder, salt, pepper, lemon juice and reserved soaked bread into mixing bowl and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 6<b>.","Lightly grease hands with oil. Form mixture into 16 balls (approx. 1 tablespoon each) and place into Varoma dish and onto Varoma tray. Set aside. Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Place remaining 500 g water into mixing bowl. Place Varoma into position, secure Varoma lid and steam <b>20 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b> or until balls are cooked through.","Transfer strained yoghurt into a small bowl. Add reserved parsley mixture, season with salt and pepper and stir to combine. Serve fish balls immediately. "]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["250 g natural yoghurt","40 g day old bread (approx. 1 slice), cut into pieces (2 cm)","540 g water","4 sprigs fresh flat-leaf parsley, leaves only","2 spring onions\/shallots, trimmed and cut into pieces (approx. 4 cm)","½ lemon zested, no white pith, and juiced","400 g firm white fish fillets, cut into pieces (2 cm) (see Tips)","1 egg","2 pinches chilli powder","1 tsp salt, plus extra to season","½ tsp ground black pepper, plus extra to season","extra virgin olive oil, for forming balls"]}],"id":"r120348","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-YkNwEWmJ6vc\/XZVP2nQAbII\/AAAAAAAAc9Y\/58B9kqSVXj08ccp8n85LmftzjTdW_YGFACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_GR1CG1SZXp4S1jQZ.png","title":"Fish balls with yoghurt sauce","publishedAt":"2017-01-15T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"26.3 g","fat":"9.9 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"8 g","calories":"971 kJ \/ 231 kcal"},"usefulItems":"small bowl , nut bag or fine mesh sieve, ceramic or glass bowl, bowl, serving platter, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["You can use any type of firm white fish fillet such as barramundi, snapper or ling in this recipe.<br>","For a different flavour, try replacing the parsley with tarragon or coriander.","For a more complete meal, serve with a fresh green salad. <br>"],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","1h 50m","4 portions"]}